  <prompt>
    Author **ADR-031 (stage lifecycle pattern)** in both forms: concise at `.claude/adr/ADR-031-stage-lifecycle.md`
    (~100-150 lines) and full at `docs/adr/ADR-031-stage-lifecycle.md`. ADR-031 codifies the R2-invented
    stage lifecycle (load / hydrate / ready / refresh / error) used by widgets and Code Pages. This
    documentation task **codifies an existing pattern** — do NOT propose behavior changes. Update
    `.claude/adr/INDEX.md`. Note: this ADR is the foundation that task 016 D-2 amends with the
    "Heavy library handling" subsection.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Architecture documentation author. Same dual-form ADR style as A-2a (task 012). Source of truth is
    the existing widget / page lifecycle code; the ADR documents constraints that consumers must obey.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three artifacts: (1) `.claude/adr/ADR-031-stage-lifecycle.md` (concise, ~100-150 lines, MUST/MUST NOT,
    stage definitions, transitions, code pointers); (2) `docs/adr/ADR-031-stage-lifecycle.md` (full form
    with Context / Decision / Consequences / Alternatives Considered / References); (3) updated
    `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` with ADR-031 entry. Both forms MUST cross-link. Task 016 (D-2) appends a
    "Heavy library handling" subsection — leave the structure amenable to that amendment.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec DR-04 + plan §4 Phase 1 A-2: ADR-031 captures the stage lifecycle pattern (R2-invented) that
      governs how widgets and Code Pages transition through load → hydrate → ready → refresh → error
      states. R3 used this extensively (Calendar widget, Daily Briefing, workspace tabs). Task 016 D-2
      will amend this ADR with a "Heavy library handling" subsection covering singlefile-vs-lazy-import
      incompatibility (R3 bundle-size investigation). Author the base ADR cleanly first; amendment lands
      separately.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
