  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">ADR-031 codifies an EXISTING pattern — do NOT propose new stages or new transition rules. Source of truth is the existing code.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Concise form (`.claude/adr/`) MUST be ~100-150 lines with explicit MUST / MUST NOT rules.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Full form (`docs/adr/`) MUST include Context / Decision / Consequences / Alternatives Considered / References.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Stage definitions MUST be enumerated: load (initial fetch), hydrate (apply persisted state), ready (interactive), refresh (re-fetch on demand), error (fault).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Document MUST be structured to accept the task 016 D-2 amendment cleanly — leave room for a "Heavy library handling" subsection. Do not write content that 016 will need to delete.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Both forms MUST cross-link. `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` MUST include ADR-031 with links to both.</constraint>
  </constraints>

